#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc82:1.1.0"
msgid "82. Pariṇāmanasikkhāpada"
msgstr ""
"<hgroup><h1 id=\"Bu-Pc.82\">Monks’ Confession 82: the training rule on "
"diverting</h1></hgroup>"

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1, pts-vp-pli4.156
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc82:1.1.1"
msgid ""
"Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa "
"ārāme."
msgstr ""
"<h2 id=\"nidana\">Origin story</h2><p><a class=\"pts-cs\" id=\"Bu-Pc.82.1\""
">Bu-Pc.82.1</a><a class=\"pts-vp-en\" id=\"BD.3.67\">BD.3.67</a><a class"
"=\"wt-pa\">1435</a>At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the "
"Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc82:1.1.2"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena sāvatthiyaṃ aññatarassa pūgassa saṃghassa "
"sacīvarabhattaṃ paṭiyattaṃ hoti—"
msgstr ""
"At that time an association had prepared a meal together with robe-cloth for "
"the Order. They said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc82:1.1.3"
msgid "“bhojetvā cīvarena acchādessāmā”ti."
msgstr "“After giving the food, we’ll offer the robe-cloth.”</p>"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc82:1.1.4"
msgid "Atha kho chabbaggiyā bhikkhū yena so pūgo tenupasaṅkamiṃsu;"
msgstr "<p>But the monks from the group of six went to that association"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc82:1.1.5"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā taṃ pūgaṃ etadavocuṃ—"
msgstr "and said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc82:1.1.6"
msgid "“dethāvuso, imāni cīvarāni imesaṃ bhikkhūnan”ti."
msgstr "“Sirs, give this robe-cloth to these monks.”</p>"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc82:1.1.7"
msgid "“Na mayaṃ, bhante, dassāma."
msgstr "<p>“Venerables, we can’t do that."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc82:1.1.8"
msgid "Amhākaṃ saṃghassa anuvassaṃ sacīvarabhikkhā paññattā”ti."
msgstr ""
"We’ve prepared our annual alms-offering together with robe-cloth for the "
"Order.”</p>"

#. VAR: bhattā → bhaddāni (bj) | bhaddā (mr)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc82:1.1.9"
msgid "“Bahū, āvuso, saṃghassa dāyakā, bahū saṃghassa bhattā."
msgstr "<p>“The Order has many donors and supporters."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc82:1.1.10"
msgid "Ime tumhe nissāya tumhe sampassantā idha viharanti."
msgstr ""
"But since these monks are staying here, they depend on you and look to you "
"for support."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc82:1.1.11"
msgid "Tumhe ce imesaṃ na dassatha, atha ko carahi imesaṃ dassati?"
msgstr ""
"If you don’t give to them, <a class=\"pts-vp-pi\" id=\"Vin.4.156\""
">Vin.4.156</a> who will?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc82:1.1.12"
msgid "Dethāvuso, imāni cīvarāni imesaṃ bhikkhūnan”ti."
msgstr "So give them this robe-cloth.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc82:1.1.13"
msgid ""
"Atha kho so pūgo chabbaggiyehi bhikkhūhi nippīḷiyamāno yathāpaṭiyattaṃ "
"cīvaraṃ chabbaggiyānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ datvā saṃghaṃ bhattena parivisi."
msgstr ""
"Being pressured by the monks from the group of six, that association gave "
"the prepared robe-cloth to those other monks from the group of six and "
"served the food to the Order.</p>"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc82:1.1.14"
msgid ""
"Ye te bhikkhū jānanti saṃghassa sacīvarabhattaṃ paṭiyattaṃ “na ca jānanti "
"chabbaggiyānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ dinnan”ti te evamāhaṃsu—"
msgstr ""
"<p>The monks who knew that a meal together with robe-cloth had been prepared "
"for the Order, but not that the robe-cloth had been given to those monks "
"from the group six, said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc82:1.1.15"
msgid "“oṇojethāvuso, saṃghassa cīvaran”ti."
msgstr "“You may offer the robe-cloth.”</p>"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc82:1.1.16"
msgid "“Natthi, bhante."
msgstr "<p>“Venerables, there isn’t any."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc82:1.1.17"
msgid ""
"Yathāpaṭiyattaṃ cīvaraṃ ayyā chabbaggiyā ayyānaṃ chabbaggiyānaṃ "
"pariṇāmesun”ti."
msgstr ""
"The robe-cloth we had prepared were diverted by the monks from the group of "
"six to other monks from the group of six.”</p>"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc82:1.1.18"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1436</a>The monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc82:1.1.19"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized those monks,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc82:1.1.20"
msgid ""
"“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū jānaṃ saṃghikaṃ lābhaṃ pariṇataṃ "
"puggalassa pariṇāmessantī”ti … pe …"
msgstr ""
"“How can the monks from the group of six divert to an individual things they "
"know were intended for the Order?” …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc82:1.1.21"
msgid ""
"“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, jānaṃ saṃghikaṃ lābhaṃ pariṇataṃ puggalassa "
"pariṇāmethā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"<a class=\"pts-vp-en\" id=\"BD.3.68\">BD.3.68</a>“Is it true, monks, that "
"you did this?”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc82:1.1.22"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc82:1.1.23"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked them, “…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc82:1.1.24"
msgid ""
"kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, jānaṃ saṃghikaṃ lābhaṃ pariṇataṃ "
"puggalassa pariṇāmessatha."
msgstr ""
"Foolish men, how can you divert to an individual things that you know were "
"intended for the Order?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc82:1.1.25"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc82:1.1.26"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:</p>"

#. HTML: </p><p><b class="rule">
#. REF: sc3
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc82:1.1.27"
msgid ""
"“Yo pana bhikkhu jānaṃ saṃghikaṃ lābhaṃ pariṇataṃ puggalassa pariṇāmeyya, "
"pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr ""
"<h2 id=\"pannatti\">Final ruling</h2><p class=\"rule\"><a class=\"wt-pa\""
">1437</a>‘If a monk diverts to an individual something that he knows was "
"intended for the Order, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”</p>"

#. HTML: </b></p><p><b class="term">
#. REF: sc4
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc82:2.1.1"
msgid "Yo panāti"
msgstr ""
"<h2 id=\"pada\">Definitions</h2><p><a class=\"pts-cs\" id=\"Bu-Pc.82.2\""
"></a><a class=\"pts-cs\" id=\"Bu-Pc.82.2.1\">Bu-Pc.82.2.1</a><a class=\"wt-"
"pa\">1438</a><term>A</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc82:2.1.2"
msgid "yo yādiso … pe …"
msgstr "<gloss>whoever …</gloss>"

#. HTML: </b><b class="term">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc82:2.1.3"
msgid "bhikkhūti"
msgstr "<term>Monk</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc82:2.1.4"
msgid "… pe …"
msgstr "<gloss>…"

#. HTML: </b>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc82:2.1.5"
msgid "ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti."
msgstr ""
"The monk who has been given the full ordination by a complete Order through "
"a procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is "
"unchallengeable and fit to stand—this sort of monk is meant in this "
"case.</gloss></p>"

#. HTML: </p><p><b class="term">
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc82:2.1.6"
msgid "Jānāti nāma"
msgstr "<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1439</a><term>He knows</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc82:2.1.7"
msgid "sāmaṃ vā jānāti, aññe vā tassa ārocenti, so vā āroceti."
msgstr ""
"<gloss>he knows by himself or others have told him or the donor has told "
"him.<span class=\"note\">*<fn>The last of these three ways of knowing "
"presumably refers to the donor having told him directly. See discussion in "
"note to Relinquishment 30, <ref>MS.1.2425</ref>.</fn></span></gloss></p>"

#. HTML: </b></p><p><b class="term">
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc82:2.1.8"
msgid "Saṃghikaṃ nāma"
msgstr "<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1440</a><term>For the Order</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc82:2.1.9"
msgid "saṃghassa dinnaṃ hoti pariccattaṃ."
msgstr "<gloss>given to the Order, given up to the Order.</gloss></p>"

#. HTML: </b></p><p><b class="term">
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc82:2.1.10"
msgid "Lābho nāma"
msgstr "<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1441</a><term>Something</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc82:2.1.11"
msgid ""
"cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārā, antamaso "
"cuṇṇapiṇḍopi, dantakaṭṭhampi, dasikasuttampi."
msgstr ""
"<gloss>robe-cloth, almsfood, a dwelling, and medicine; even just bath "
"powder, a toothbrush, or a piece of string.</gloss></p>"

#. HTML: </b></p><p><b class="term">
#. REF: sc8
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc82:2.1.12"
msgid "Pariṇataṃ nāma"
msgstr "<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1442</a><term>Intended</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc82:2.1.13"
msgid ""
"“dassāma karissāmā”ti vācā bhinnā hoti, taṃ puggalassa pariṇāmeti, āpatti "
"pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"<gloss>if they have said, “We will give/we will prepare,” and he diverts it "
"to an individual, he commits an offense entailing confession.</gloss></p>"

#. HTML: </b></p><p>
#. REF: sc9, pts-vp-pli4.157
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc82:2.2.1"
msgid "Pariṇate pariṇatasaññī puggalassa pariṇāmeti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"<h2 id=\"cakka\">Permutations</h2><p><a class=\"pts-cs\" id=\"Bu-Pc.82.2.2\""
">Bu-Pc.82.2.2</a><a class=\"wt-pa\">1443</a>If it is intended for the Order "
"and he perceives it as such, and he diverts it to an individual, he commits "
"an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc82:2.2.2"
msgid "Pariṇate vematiko puggalassa pariṇāmeti, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is intended for the Order, but he is unsure if it is, and he diverts "
"it to an individual, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc82:2.2.3"
msgid "Pariṇate apariṇatasaññī puggalassa pariṇāmeti, anāpatti."
msgstr ""
"If it is intended for the Order, but he does not perceives it as such, and "
"he diverts it to an individual, there is no offense.</p>"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc82:2.2.4"
msgid ""
"Saṃghassa pariṇataṃ aññasaṃghassa vā cetiyassa vā pariṇāmeti, āpatti "
"dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"<p>If it is intended for one Order and he diverts it to another Order or to "
"a shrine, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc82:2.2.5"
msgid ""
"Cetiyassa pariṇataṃ aññacetiyassa vā saṃghassa vā puggalassa vā pariṇāmeti, "
"āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is <a class=\"pts-vp-en\" id=\"BD.3.69\">BD.3.69</a> intended for one "
"shrine and he diverts it to another shrine or to a Order or to an "
"individual, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc82:2.2.6"
msgid ""
"Puggalassa pariṇataṃ aññapuggalassa vā saṃghassa vā cetiyassa vā pariṇāmeti, "
"āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is intended for an individual and he diverts it to another individual "
"or to a Order or to a shrine, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.</p>"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc82:2.2.7"
msgid "Apariṇate pariṇatasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"<p>If it is not intended for the Order, but he perceives it as intended for "
"the Order, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc82:2.2.8"
msgid "Apariṇate vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is not intended for the Order, <a class=\"pts-vp-pi\" id=\"Vin.4.157\""
">Vin.4.157</a> but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong "
"conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc82:2.2.9"
msgid "Apariṇate apariṇatasaññī, anāpatti."
msgstr ""
"If it is not intended for the Order and he does not perceive it as such, "
"there is no offense.</p>"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc10
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc82:2.3.1"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr ""
"<h2 id=\"anapatti\">Non-offenses</h2><p><a class=\"pts-cs\" id=\"Bu-Pc.82.2."
"3\">Bu-Pc.82.2.3</a><a class=\"wt-pa\">1444</a>There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc82:2.3.2"
msgid "“kattha demā”ti pucchīyamāno—"
msgstr "if being asked,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc82:2.3.3"
msgid ""
"“yattha tumhākaṃ deyyadhammo paribhogaṃ vā labheyya paṭisaṅkhāraṃ vā "
"labheyya ciraṭṭhitiko vā assa yattha vā pana tumhākaṃ cittaṃ pasīdati tattha "
"dethā”ti bhaṇati, ummattakassa, ādikammikassāti."
msgstr ""
"“Where may we give?” he says, “Give where your gift goes towards equipment/"
"goes towards repairs/where it will last for a long time/where you feel "
"inspired;” if he is insane; if he is the first offender.</p>"

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsutta">
#. REF: sc11
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc82:2.3.4"
msgid "Pariṇāmanasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ dvādasamaṃ."
msgstr ""
"<hr><p class=\"endsutta\"><a class=\"wt-pa\">1445</a>The twelfth rule, the "
"training rule on diverting, is finished.</p>"

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc82:2.3.5"
msgid "Sahadhammikavaggo aṭṭhamo."
msgstr ""
"<p class=\"endchapter\">The eighth chapter on legitimately is finished.</p>"

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection summary">
#. REF: sc12
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc82:2.3.6"
msgid "Tassuddānaṃ"
msgstr "<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1446</a>This is the summary:</p>"

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. REF: sc13
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc82:2.3.7"
msgid "Sahadhamma vivaṇṇañca,"
msgstr ""
"<p><uddana><a class=\"wt-pa\">1447</a>Legitimately, and disparaging,<br>"

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc82:2.3.8"
msgid "mohāpanaṃ pahārakaṃ;"
msgstr "Deception, striking;<br>"

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc82:2.3.9"
msgid "Talasatti amūlañca,"
msgstr "Threatening with the palm of the hand, and groundlessly,<br>"

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc82:2.3.10"
msgid "sañcicca ca upassuti;"
msgstr "And intentionally, eavesdropping;<br>"

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc82:2.3.11"
msgid "Paṭibāhana chandañca,"
msgstr "Blocking, and consent,<br>"

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc82:2.3.12"
msgid "dabbañca pariṇāmananti."
msgstr "And Dabba, diverting.</uddana></p>"
